--- !u!114 &2767970370104310347
MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: e5800231a05eaae43b00503881229245, type: 3}
  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  originalLanguage: en
  translationSets:
  - counter: 75
    languageCode: en
    translations:
    - id: 0
      language: en
      text: Jimbo
    - id: 1
      language: en
      text: Hello! I'm looking for new adventures, but your board outside inn is
        empty. Have you heard of any work in the area?
    - id: 2
      language: en
      text: Bartender
    - id: 3
      language: en
      text: Welcome to my inn, traveler. I see that good Viridan helped you to come
        to our town. Unfortunetly, all quests are done. There was another traveler,
        mighty barbarian with great sword any mighty head, who did all of them.
    - id: 4
      language: en
      text: Damn, here we go again... So what, should we go to next town?
    - id: 5
      language: en
      text: Ask him again, maybe we can talk to this barbarian? Maybe he has some
        job to do?
    - id: 6
      language: en
      text: Okay then, say goodbye and let's move on.
    - id: 7
      language: en
      text: Narrator
    - id: 8
      language: en
      text: Are you sure? I think we should go to that barbarian. Maybe we can train
        with him or something? As a patron, you should do everything you can to make
        sure your man trains and gains fame.
    - id: 9
      language: en
      text: You again? We don't need your help. Trust me, I know what I am doing.
    - id: 10
      language: en
      text: Maybe you are right. Hey Jimbo, ask him about this barbarian, where he
        is, what is his name, everything.
    - id: 11
      language: en
      text: Why are we still here?
    - id: 12
      language: en
      text: Hello, i've heard that someone from your village has problem to solve.
    - id: 13
      language: en
      text: 'Welcome to my inn, traveler. I see that good Viridan helped you to come
        to our town. Yes, you are right, there is old barbarian who need help. He
        lives in old brown house, to the north from inn. '
    - id: 14
      language: en
      text: Great, i will visit him.
    - id: 15
      language: en
      text: Do you need something more?
    - id: 16
      language: en
      text: Were there any rumors going around?
    - id: 17
      language: en
      text: I want something to eat.
    - id: 18
      language: en
      text: See you.
    - id: 19
      language: en
      text: "Someone dug up the Black Knight\u2019s grave in the old cemetery\u2026
        but the coffin was empty."
    - id: 20
      language: en
      text: "Bob, an old miner, swears something\u2019s glowing deep in the abandoned
        mine \u2014 not gold, something brighter. He hasn\u2019t been seen since"
    - id: 21
      language: en
      text: "The wizard across the river is looking for someone to bring him \u2018something
        living\u2026 and cursed.\u2019 Best not to ask why..."
    - id: 22
      language: en
      text: "An innkeeper up north says something scratches at his doors every night\u2026
        but the rooms are always empty."
    - id: 23
      language: en
      text: We have potatoes, turnip and corn.
    - id: 24
      language: en
      text: Give me potato.
    - id: 25
      language: en
      text: Turnip sounds good.
    - id: 26
      language: en
      text: I'd like some corn, please.
    - id: 27
      language: en
      text: Give me potato. *2gp*
    - id: 28
      language: en
      text: Turnip sounds good. *3gp*
    - id: 29
      language: en
      text: I'd like some corn, please. *5gp*
    - id: 30
      language: en
      text: I can't afford it, I'll come back when I get some gold.
    - id: 31
      language: en
      text: We have pumpkins. Would you like to buy some?
    - id: 32
      language: en
      text: Yes, please. *10gp*
    - id: 33
      language: en
      text: Here you are.
    - id: 34
      language: en
      text: Player
    - id: 35
      language: en
      text: Good morning sir, I came from the continent because I heard that you
        have problems in the city. Who's in charge here?
    - id: 36
      language: en
      text: Welcome to my inn! First time in Moonveil?
    - id: 37
      language: en
      text: Actually yes, I've never been to this part of Lunaris.
    - id: 38
      language: en
      text: Do you need any help?
    - id: 39
      language: en
      text: Buy something (TODO)
    - id: 40
      language: en
      text: Some day, shop will be here.
    - id: 41
      language: en
      text: Actually, since you asked, I have a big request, I will pay.
    - id: 42
      language: en
      text: Ok
    - id: 43
      language: en
      text: 'Bring me pumpkins, please!

'
    - id: 44
      language: en
      text: I can't leave the inn because there are too many guests. Maybe you could
        go to the warehouse to the west of the village, that big brown building.
        There are chests there with pumpkins inside. Could you bring me 8?
    - id: 45
      language: en
      text: I found an advertisement that there is a thief in the city.
    - id: 46
      language: en
      text: Yes, he robbed Rolf's field. He had beautiful corn, and the thief took
        the best. Maybe he knows something.
    - id: 47
      language: en
      text: Ok, I will check his farm.
    - id: 48
      language: en
      text: I would like to ask you one more thing.
    - id: 49
      language: en
      text: "How are you\t"
    - id: 50
      language: en
      text: I have quest!
    - id: 51
      language: en
      text: We talked about this
    - id: 52
      language: en
      text: I know something about thief!
    - id: 53
      language: en
      text: Do you know something about this task?
    - id: 54
      language: en
      text: See you!
    - id: 55
      language: en
      text: I heard you are looking for a criminal.
    - id: 56
      language: en
      text: Yes!
    - id: 57
      language: en
      text: Like I said before...
    - id: 58
      language: en
      text: Just fine, thanks.
    - id: 59
      language: en
      text: How are you?
    - id: 60
      language: en
      text: How can I help you, sir?
    - id: 61
      language: en
      text: Go to Rolf. Maybe he knows something.
    - id: 62
      language: en
      text: I don't need help at the moment, but ask around the village, maybe someone
        else will need it.
    - id: 63
      language: en
      text: Hey, I have pumpkins.
    - id: 64
      language: en
      text: Thank you so much!
    - id: 65
      language: en
      text: Thank you, but I don't need more pumpkins. You can keep them.
    - id: 66
      language: en
      text: I need to ask you for a favor, obviously not for free.
    - id: 67
      language: en
      text: Rolf said he saw the thief running towards the warehouse.
    - id: 68
      language: en
      text: Sure, here's the key. The warehouse is in the western part of town, you'll
        definitely find it. It's a large, brown building.
    - id: 69
      language: en
      text: Thank you! I will come back soon!
    - id: 70
      language: en
      text: I got rid of the bandit, he didn't want to cooperate.
    - id: 71
      language: en
      text: 'Great, thank you very much. Here is a reward! '
    - id: 72
      language: en
      text: Welcome to my inn.
    - id: 73
      language: en
      text: This is where you will meet the heroes and villagers you will save.
    - id: 74
      language: en
      text: This is where you will meet  heroes and villagers you will save.
